    "abstract": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>The COVID-19 pandemic caused by SARS-CoV-2 started in fall 2019. A range of different mammalian species, including farmed mink, have been confirmed as susceptible to infection with this virus. We report here the spillover of mink-adapted SARS-CoV-2 from farmed mink to humans after extensive adaptation that lasted at least 3 months. We found the presence of four mutations in the S gene (that gave rise to variant: G75V, M177T, Y453F and C1247F) and others in an isolate obtained from SARS-CoV-2 positive patient.</jats:p>",
